\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As Eddie and Will sat onto a bench outside the library, the weight of their shared sorrow momentarily lifted by the simple act of companionship}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94Ed!\u8221\'94 Ashley shouted from the distant lawn, her voice is distant and he looked so small from across the lawn,}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As she closes the distance Ashley's footsteps echo against the pavement as she gets closer between them. Her arrival is unexpected but welcome, a ray of light piercing through the darkness of uncertainty.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie spotted Ashley first, her dark cloak fluttering like a battle standard as she crossed the quad. Then his stomach dropped. Two figures trailed behind her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 one with perfectly coiled platinum braids, the other a hulking shadow. Even from this distance, Christine's prissy gait and Geralt's lumbering steps were unmistakable.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Well shit," Will muttered, cracking his knuckles. "Thought we wouldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t deal with them again."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Ashley took a moment to catch her breath, gratefully accepting the drink Will offered and sat next to her on the stairs. "I spoke with my advocacy group," she explained, downing a large gulp of the cool liquid. "I thnk I know how can we find Madeleine."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 "Let me guess," Eddie cut in, clapping slowly. "Brilliant plan, Ash. Truly inspired. But why in the nine hells are\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 they}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~here?" He jabbed a finger at Christine, who was examining her manicure with practiced boredom.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Christine, here is\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8220\'93 But before Ashley could finish her sentence, she was cut off.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Christine snapped her head up, eyes flashing. "Because unlike\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 some}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~people, I actually care about finding the missing." She thrust a poster at Eddie's chest\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a grinning dark-haired boy labeled\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Dominic Laverne: Last Seen Near South Gate}{\f0\fs24\b0 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie's fingers crumpled the edges. He remembered Dominic\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 quiet transfer student, always sketching in the library alcoves. The realization hit like a gut punch: this wasn't just about Madeleine anymore.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Ashley stepped between them like a referee. "We need everyone who\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 "}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Still playing the hero, Ed?" Christine's laugh was all venom. "What, your little girlfriend\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 "}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie's chair screeched as he stood. "Finish that sentence, sorceress. I dare you."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 "ENOUGH!" }{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Ashley slammed her staff between them. }{\f0\fs24\b0 The oakwood hummed with residual magic. "Dominic. Madeleine. The twenty-three others on this list\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 " She yanked a Campus Watch dossier from her bag, pages fluttering like wounded birds. "They're not coming home unless we work together."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Think about it," Ashley continued, her voice gaining strength. "There must be others who have put up missing person posters around campus other than us, people with contact information. We could reach out to them, offer them a chance to join forces. We wouldn't be an army of Royal Paladins, of course, but we will be driven by a common purpose \endash  to bring down the Black Hand and find the people they love."}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie's jaw worked. Christine's perfect nails dug into Dominic's poster. The quad's chatter\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 laughter, spell practice, someone playing a lute badly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 felt obscenely loud against their silence.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Finally, Christine smoothed her robes with exaggerated care. "My father's office has access to the citywide missing persons registry." She said it like granting a royal favor.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Will snorted. "And what do\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 you}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~want, princess?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Same as you." Christine's gaze flicked to Dominic's photo, just for a heartbeat. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Ashley's grin was all teeth. "Then we start calling every name in this file. Tonight."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The grudging nods took a lifetime. But when Christine turned away, Eddie caught the tremor in her hands\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the same one he'd been hiding since yesterday. Maybe hate could wait. For now.}
